<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Species in the 
<taxonomicName authority="Butomomyza" class="Insecta" family="Boraginaceae" genus="Agromyza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="(Butomomyza) subsp. subgenus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" species="angulata" subGenus="Butomomyza" subSpecies="subgenus">subgenus Butomomyza</taxonomicName>
, as defined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Nowakowski, JT" journalOrPublisher="Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="633 - 661" refId="B182" refString="Nowakowski, JT, 1967. Vorlaeufige Mitteilung zu einer Monographie der europaeischen Arten der Gattung Cerodontha Rond. (Diptera, Agromyzidae). Polskie Pismo Entomologiczne 37: 633 - 661" title="Vorlaeufige Mitteilung zu einer Monographie der europaeischen Arten der Gattung Cerodontha Rond. (Diptera, Agromyzidae)." volume="37" year="1967">Nowakowski (1967)</bibRefCitation>
, are recognisable by a lunule that is as wide as high or slightly higher, and at least in the Nearctic species examined here, the acrostichal setae are present and the body is often pale brown to brown. Furthermore, the shape of the lunule is subtriangular with bowed sides and often a pointed apex, and the surface is not textured, but covered with a minute velvety pubescence. Larvae also have one pair of rounded areas flanking the anus that are covered with black cuticular teeth that may reach the posterior spiracles. There are more than two dozen species, mostly in the north temperate regions, where they are known to mine in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cyperaceae" genus="Agromyza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Cyperaceae</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Poaceae" genus="Agromyza" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Poaceae</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Zlobin, VV" journalOrPublisher="An International Journal of Dipterological Research" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="113 - 122" refId="B309" refString="Zlobin, VV, 2001. Review of the mining flies of the subgenus Cerodontha Rondani. XII. Oriental Butomomyza species (Diptera: Agromyzidae). An International Journal of Dipterological Research 12 (2): 113 - 122" title="Review of the mining flies of the subgenus Cerodontha Rondani. XII. Oriental Butomomyza species (Diptera: Agromyzidae)." volume="12" year="2001">Zlobin 2001</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
